  "explanation": "The defendant, an accountant with no prior criminal history, embezzled $25,000 from their employer to pay off personal debts. While this represents a serious breach of trust and fiduciary duty, mitigating factors must be considered, specifically the lack of a criminal record and the proactive effort to partially repay the embezzled funds. Under typical sentencing patterns, a non-violent first-time offender in this financial range warrants a brief period of incarceration to serve as a deterrent, combined with probation and full restitution requirements. Therefore, a sentence of 3 months of incarceration is deemed appropriate and sufficient.",
